‚ü¶ Built-in list operations demonstration.

  `‚Ü¶` and `‚ä≥` are canonical pure operators.
  Use `‚äï` for ordered reductions.
‚üß

‚ü¶ Map: [1,2,3] ‚Ü¶ Œª(x:Int)=>Int=x*2 ‚üß
ŒªdoubleAll(xs:[Int])=>[Int]=xs‚Ü¶Œª(x:Int)=>Int=x*2

‚ü¶ Chaining: filter, then map ‚üß
ŒªfilterThenMap(xs:[Int])=>[Int]=(xs‚ä≥Œª(x:Int)=>Bool=x>0)‚Ü¶Œª(x:Int)=>Int=x*x

‚ü¶ Filter: [1,2,3,4,5] ‚ä≥ Œª(x:Int)=>Bool=x>2 ‚üß
ŒªkeepLarge(xs:[Int])=>[Int]=xs‚ä≥Œª(x:Int)=>Bool=x>2

Œªmain()=>Int=sum(([1,2,3,4,5]:[Int]))

‚ü¶ Fold: [1,2,3] ‚äï Œª(acc:Int,x:Int)=>Int=acc+x ‚äï 0 ‚üß
Œªsum(xs:[Int])=>Int=xs‚äï(Œª(acc:Int,x:Int)=>Int=acc+x)‚äï0
